cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SC 

This paper is about formalizing a model language for expressing tensor operations. It is likely to be categorized under Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it deals with the development of a language for tensor manipulation. It also involves machine learning applications, which suggests a possible categorization under Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of high-dimensional data and multi-dimensional tensors suggests a possible categorization under Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the implementation of the model language, which suggests a possible categorization under Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance benefits of an alternative implementation, which suggests a possible categorization under Scientific Computing (cs.SC).
